Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the
@echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(grated). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Once boiling,
add the @penne pasta{200%g} to the water, simmer until cooked,
~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan and stir through a
little oil to stop it sticking together.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is
hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and stir-fry until it releases its lovely red oil,
~{1-2%minutes}. Don't let it take on too much colour! Pour the chorizo and all
its oil into a #bowl{} and add the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and the
@olive oil{1%tbsp}. Add a grind of @ground black pepper{1%grind}, stir to coat
the crumbs in the oil and leave to the side.

Put your frying pan back on medium-high heat. Add the @olive oil{1%tsp} and
the shallot. Stir-fry until the shallot is soft, ~{3-4%minutes} then stir in
the @plain flour{16%g}. Cook until it forms a paste consistency,
~{1-2%minutes}. Gradually, stir in the @water{200%ml} and the
@chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @dried thyme{1%tsp} and cheddar to the sauce and stir until the cheese
is melted. Taste and add @?salt{} and @?ground black pepper{} if it needs it.
Add the pasta to the sauce and stir to combine with a splash of @?water{} to
loosen if you need to. Pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle the chorizo
crumb evenly over the top, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until the
crumbs are golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from your oven.
Meanwhile, wash out your frying pan and pop back on medium high heat.

Add a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} to your frying pan and once hot, add the
@tenderstem broccoli{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry
until starting to char, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the @garlic clove{1}(grated) to the
pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} longer, then add a splash of @water{} and
cover the pan with a #lid{} or #kitchen foil{}. Lower the heat to medium and
steam the broccoli until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Spoon the penne 'n cheese into #bowls{} and serve the broccoli alongside. Enjoy!

> Like the classic mac 'n cheese, our recipe is packed full of cheesy deliciousness
> but with some added extras. The chorizo crumb adds a depth of smoky flavour and
> creates a crisp topping, the perfect counterpart to the ultra-creamy and silky
> cheese sauce. To finish, stir through garlicky tenderstem broccoli and asparagus
> to elevate this pasta dish from low-key to lavish in an instant.